            <bio>
               <p>Jesse Gleason, Ph.D., is an Assistant Professor of TESOL and Spanish at Southern Connecticut State University. Her teaching and research interests include classroom discourse, content-based instruction, task-based language learning, blended and online learning, language assessment and systemic functional linguistic (SFL) approaches to language and literacy. She is especially interested in how teachers and students can harness technology for optimal second and foreign language learning. Her current ideas on these topics can be found in a number of peer reviewed articles in journals such as <italic>System, Hispania, Foreign Language Annals</italic>, and the <italic>Canadian Journal of Applied Linguistics</italic>.</p>
